everyone I used to talk to

3
00:00:06.310 --> 00:00:09.710
considered squatters
to be transgressors.

4
00:00:11.220 --> 00:00:15.650
They'd misjudge it completely.

5
00:00:15.650 --> 00:00:18.740
You see, they'd been
influenced by the media.

6
00:00:18.740 --> 00:00:24.620
Living in a squat, as I came
to realize, and which is natural,

7
00:00:24.620 --> 00:00:28.650
is something that only people
really in need do, who're

8
00:00:28.650 --> 00:00:32.310
really struggling
for a place to live.

9
00:00:32.310 --> 00:00:34.740
The squats belong to the media

10
00:00:34.740 --> 00:00:38.400
and to the dominating class.

11
00:00:38.400 --> 00:00:45.200
So they use information
the way they want it to be.

12
00:00:45.200 --> 00:00:50.310
to sustain the domination in
the hands of some elite, you see?

13
00:00:50.310 --> 00:00:53.050
They'll never
show the true situation

14
00:00:53.050 --> 00:00:58.140
of people who are living in
a squat and struggling for a home.

15
00:00:58.140 --> 00:01:00.450
They're humble, working people.

16
00:01:00.450 --> 00:01:04.620
And they'll show an image completely
distorted from the reality image.

17
00:01:04.620 --> 00:01:07.000
The media is today what I believe

18
00:01:07.000 --> 00:01:10.110
to be the opposite of what
it was supposed to be.

19
00:01:10.110 --> 00:01:14.000
Instead of being sensationalist

20
00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:17.220
and providing false information,

21
00:01:17.220 --> 00:01:21.370
it should show us real facts.

22
00:01:21.370 --> 00:01:23.620
It's definitely not what happens.

23
